{
  "texts": [
    "Under this angle, we review and discuss important results on representing, designing and analyzing RC systems.",
    "The mathematical abstraction of an RC can generally be described in the language of dynamical systems, as follows.",
    "Consider a coupled system of equations Δx = Fðx; u; pÞ, y = Gðx; u; qÞ:",
    "Here the operator Δ acting on x becomes dx dt for a continuous-time system, x(t + 1)x(t) for a discrete-time system, and a compound of these two operations for a hybrid system.",
    "Additionally, u 2 R d, x 2 R n, and y 2 R m are generally referred to as the input, internal state and output of the system, respectively, with vector field F, output function G and parameters p (fixed) and q (learnable) representing"
  ]
}